/*
 * HapticClient.cpp
 * ================
 * CLIENT side – runs on PC-B (has Novint Falcon #2).
 *
 * Mirror image of the server:
 *   1. Listens on 0.0.0.0:4000 for HapticPacket from server
 *   2. Applies received server position as force to local Falcon (if FB on)
 *   3. Reads local Falcon position at 1 kHz
 *   4. Sends HapticPacket back to SERVER_IP:4000 (if TX enabled)
 *   5. Shows TWO candlestick charts side by side:
 *        LEFT  = remote haptic data (what SERVER Falcon is doing, RECEIVED)
 *        RIGHT = local haptic data  (what THIS Falcon is doing, SENT BACK)
 *
 * Controls: identical to server
 *   T   toggle sending data back to server
 *   R   toggle receiving from server
 *   F   toggle force feedback to local Falcon from server data
 *   +/- candle window  |  [ max  ] min  |  ESC quit
 *
 * Set SERVER_IP at the top before building.
 */

